        <div id="membershipSection" class="container4">

          <h2>Membership</h2>
          <p class="member-info">Becoming a member of the Sri Aurobindo Society is a personal committment.<br>

            Members are eligible to receive regular literature and information from us and communication regarding our
            work.
            Those who opt for it would receive our monthly journal All India Magazine at their registered address.<br>

            Membership to the Society is only a first step. To start with, the simple program has been suggested for the
            members.<br>
          <ul class="member-info">
            <li> Devote some time daily to study something from the writings of Sri Aurobindo and the Mother, according
              to
              the
              query within.</li>
            <li> Sit quietly for a few minutes every day and ask oneself: Why am I here? What exactly do I want to
              achieve
              in
              life? etc.</li>
            <li> Devote one hour daily for some work of the Society and do it in a selfless and unegoistic spirit.</li>
          </ul>



          <p class="member-info">You can apply for SAS Membership online or via mail. If you have any queries related to
            membership, email us at<br> <a
              href="mailto:sriaurobindosociety.wbsc@gmail.com">sriaurobindosociety.wbsc@gmail.com</a> OR
            <a href="mailto:membership@aurosociety.org">membership@aurosociety.org</a>
          </p>
